{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:47:46.610354+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 202, "prompt_tokens": 10010, "total_tokens": 10212, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 142, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7104}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "3348a02ae94445a498ab021688931a0b", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead7f-430f-7ef3-a621-ce17552bd3c6-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C01_A01", "path": "src/vidpack/runner.py"}, "id": "call_f35e1907c89b43269df2ad05", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10010, "output_tokens": 202, "total_tokens": 10212, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7104}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 142}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:47:47.493641+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:FPL6DF | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca886e6501062ae49242c9393da158c273a90050)", "id": "lc_80da1deb-3832-4bdd-9032-8187e97f23b2"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:FPL6DF | \"\"\"Build and execute ffmpeg subprocess calls based on a profile dict.\"\"\"\n| MCP:FPL6DF | from __future__ import annotations\n| MCP:FPL6DF | \n| MCP:FPL6DF | import subprocess\n| MCP:FPL6DF | from pathlib import Path\n| MCP:FPL6DF | \n| MCP:FPL6DF | \n| MCP:FPL6DF | def build_ffmpeg_command(profile: dict, input_path: Path, output_path: Path) -> list[str]:\n| MCP:FPL6DF |     \"\"\"Translate a profile dict into an ffmpeg argv list.\"\"\"\n| MCP:FPL6DF |     cmd = [\"ffmpeg\", \"-i\", str(input_path)]\n| MCP:FPL6DF | \n| MCP:FPL6DF |     container = profile[\"container\"]\n| MCP:FPL6DF |     if container == \"gif\":\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         # Single-pass palette generation. See profiles.toml note about quality.\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n| MCP:FPL6DF |     else:\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         video_codec = profile[\"video_codec\"]\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         audio_codec = profile[\"audio_codec\"]\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         cmd += [\"-c:v\", video_codec, \"-c:a\", audio_codec]\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         if \"video_bitrate\" in profile:\n| MCP:FPL6DF |             cmd += [\"-b:v\", profile[\"video_bitrate\"]]\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         if \"crf\" in profile:\n| MCP:FPL6DF |             cmd += [\"-crf\", str(profile[\"crf\"])]\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         scale = profile.get(\"scale\")\n| MCP:FPL6DF |         if scale and scale != \"source\":\n| MCP:FPL6DF |             cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"scale={scale}\"]\n| MCP:FPL6DF | \n| MCP:FPL6DF |     cmd.append(str(output_path))\n| MCP:FPL6DF |     return cmd\n| MCP:FPL6DF | \n| MCP:FPL6DF | \n| MCP:FPL6DF | def run(cmd: list[str]) -> int:\n| MCP:FPL6DF |     return subprocess.call(cmd)", "id": "lc_ea721a08-d293-43a6-818c-f4700c3f4cc2"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "214999f7-d1a4-4701-a661-b06cd341f2f1", "tool_call_id": "call_f35e1907c89b43269df2ad05", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:47:59.945818+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository's `profiles.toml` and the README documentation, the `vidpack` command offers **three encoding profiles**:\n\n| Profile | Container | Video Codec | Audio Codec | Key Characteristics |\n|---------|-----------|-------------|-------------|---------------------|\n| **`web`** | MP4 | libx264 | AAC | 720p resolution, 2 Mbps target bitrate |\n| **`archive`** | MKV | libx265 | FLAC | Source resolution, CRF 18 (visually lossless) |\n| **`gif`** | GIF | *(palette‑based)* | none | 480p‑wide, 12 fps; uses a single‑pass palette generation pipeline |\n\n**Notes:**\n- The `gif` profile does not specify a traditional video codec; instead it applies a palette‑generation filter (`fps=…,scale=…:flags=lanczos`) and writes an animated GIF.\n- Profiles are loaded at runtime from `profiles.toml`; users can edit that file to customize or add new profiles.\n- The README also mentions a `production` profile that may be included in the maintained wheel (MP4 with libx265 video and Opus audio at 1080p), but that profile is not present in the checked‑in `profiles.toml` and therefore not selectable from the repository source.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 439, "prompt_tokens": 10826, "total_tokens": 11265, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 140, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 9984}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "49c502cd61ee43739599bd30ac34dacc", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead7f-63a6-79d2-8658-80f6b45e206d-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10826, "output_tokens": 439, "total_tokens": 11265, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 9984}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 140}}}}]}}}
